00:05:13.790 --> 00:05:17.140
So Poetry Out Loud is a national
youth arts program that seeks

00:05:17.140 --> 00:05:20.810 position:56%
to foster a new generation of
literary readers and engage citizens

00:05:20.810 --> 00:05:23.350
by capitalizing on
recent trends in poetry.

00:05:23.350 --> 00:05:25.270
And those are recitation
and performance.

00:05:25.270 --> 00:05:28.770
So Poetry Out Loud encourages high
school students to learn classic

00:05:28.770 --> 00:05:31.240
and contemporary poems
through memorization

00:05:31.240 --> 00:05:33.100
and then public recitation.

00:05:33.100 --> 00:05:37.040 position:56%
So this was started as a partnership
back in 2005 between the NEA

00:05:37.040 --> 00:05:41.060
and our great partnership, The
Poetry Foundation, and 53 state

00:05:41.060 --> 00:05:43.790
and jurisdictional arts
agencies across the country,

00:05:43.790 --> 00:05:46.550
which means that the Poetry Out
Loud program is in every state,

00:05:46.550 --> 00:05:50.190
D.C. The U.S. Virgin
Islands, and Puerto Rico.

00:05:50.190 --> 00:05:54.280 position:56%
Since the program began, we have
had 3.3 million students participate

00:05:54.280 --> 00:05:57.510
and over 50,000 teachers
across the country.

00:05:57.510 --> 00:06:00.120
The program helps students
build public speaking skills

00:06:00.120 --> 00:06:02.650
and self-confidence,
but most importantly,

00:06:02.650 --> 00:06:05.930
it really helps them discover
their own creative voice.

00:06:05.930 --> 00:06:07.620
I say this every year
at the book festival,

00:06:07.620 --> 00:06:10.040
