00:13:34.410 --> 00:13:35.920
"The Golden Shovel"
by Terrance Hayes.

00:13:35.920 --> 00:13:39.210
After Gwendolyn Brooks.

00:13:39.210 --> 00:13:45.970
I. 1981. When I am so small
Da's sock covers my arm,

00:13:45.970 --> 00:13:53.950
we cruise at twilight until we
find the place the real men lean,

00:13:53.950 --> 00:13:58.780 position:56%
bloodshot and translucent with cool.

00:13:58.780 --> 00:14:06.550
His smile is a gold-plated
incantation as we drift by women

00:14:06.550 --> 00:14:11.240
on bar stools, with nothing left
in them but approachlessness.

00:14:11.240 --> 00:14:13.230
This is a school I do not know yet.

00:14:13.230 --> 00:14:21.830
But the cue sticks mean we are
rubbed by light, smooth as wood,

00:14:21.830 --> 00:14:26.730
the lurk of smoke thinned to song.

00:14:26.730 --> 00:14:31.350
We won't be out late.

00:14:31.350 --> 00:14:33.570
Standing in the middle

00:14:33.570 --> 00:14:41.120
of the streets last night
we watched the moonlit lawns

00:14:41.120 --> 00:14:46.890
and a neighbor strike
his son in the face.

00:14:46.890 --> 00:14:50.250
A shadow knocked straight.

00:14:50.250 --> 00:14:58.110
Da promised to leave me everything:
the shovel we used to bury the dog,

00:14:58.110 --> 00:15:03.700
the words he loved to
sing, his rusted pistol,

00:15:03.700 --> 00:15:06.780
his squeaky Bible, his sin.

00:15:06.780 --> 00:15:08.790
The boy's sneakers
were light on the road.

00:15:08.790 --> 00:15:16.950
We watched him run to us
looking wounded and thin.

00:15:16.950 --> 00:15:20.570
He'd been caught lying or
drinking his father's gin.

00:15:20.570 --> 00:15:24.660
He'd been defending his
ma, trying to be a man.

00:15:24.660 --> 00:15:32.600
We stood in the road, and
my father talked about jazz,

00:15:32.600 --> 00:15:37.060
how sometimes a tune
is born of outrage.

00:15:37.060 --> 00:15:40.260
By June the boy would
be locked upstate.

00:15:40.260 --> 00:15:45.890
That night we got down
on our knees in my room.

00:15:45.890 --> 00:15:47.410
If I should die before I wake.

00:15:47.410 --> 00:15:49.310
Da said to me, it will be too soon.

00:15:49.310 --> 00:15:54.590 position:56%
II. 1991 Into the tented city we go,

00:15:54.590 --> 00:15:57.710
weakened by the fire's
ethereal afterglow.

00:15:57.710 --> 00:15:59.230 position:56%
Born lost and cooler than heartache.

00:15:59.230 --> 00:16:02.130
What we know is what we know.

00:16:02.130 --> 00:16:05.550
The left hand severed and
schooled by cleverness.

00:16:05.550 --> 00:16:06.850
A plate of weekdays cooking.

00:16:06.850 --> 00:16:08.150
The hour lurking in the afterglow.

00:16:08.150 --> 00:16:09.450
A late night chant.

00:16:09.450 --> 00:16:10.750
Into the city we go.

00:16:10.750 --> 00:16:12.050
Close your eyes and strike a blow.

00:16:12.050 --> 00:16:13.350
Light can be straightened
by its shadow.

00:16:13.350 --> 00:16:14.650
What we break is what we hold.

00:16:14.650 --> 00:16:15.950
A singular blue note.

00:16:15.950 --> 00:16:17.250 position:56%
An outcry singed exiting the throat.

00:16:17.250 --> 00:16:18.550
We push until we thin, thinking
we won't creep back again.

00:16:18.550 --> 00:16:19.850
While God licks his kin, we
sing until our blood is jazz,

00:16:19.850 --> 00:16:21.150
we swing from June to June.

00:16:21.150 --> 00:16:22.450
We sweat to keep from weeping.

00:16:22.450 --> 00:16:23.750
Groomed on a diet of
hunger, we end too soon.

00:16:23.750 --> 00:16:25.550
Thank you.

